solution:
When using the distributive property, we add the product of 16 and $2x$ to the product of 16 and 5:

\begin{align*}
16(2x+5) &= 16\cdot 2x+16\cdot 5\\
&= \boxed{32x+80}
\end{align*}

Applying the order of operations gives \begin{align*}
3\cdot 3 +3(3+3) - 3^3 &= 3\cdot 3 +3(6) - 3^3\\
&= 3\cdot 3 + 3(6) - 27\\
&= 9 + 18 - 27 = \boxed{0}.
\end{align*}

